servings: 2
---

Preheat your oven to 220°C. Quarter the @new potatoes{2} and pop them on a #baking tray{} with the @chicken drumsticks{8}. 

> TIP: Use the biggest baking tray you have - there's a lot to fit on! Use two if necessary.

Zest the @lemon{1} into a #small bowl{}. Mix in the @ground turmeric{3/4%tsp}, @curry powder mix{1%tsp} and @olive oil{3%tbsp} for the spices. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then pour over the potatoes and chicken. Toss to coat evenly.

Roast the potatoes and chicken on the top shelf of your oven until the potatoes are browned and crispy and the chicken is cooked through, ~{35-40%minutes}. 

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. If using two baking trays, put one on the top shelf and one on the middle and remember to swap them round halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{2} and cut into 1cm thick slices. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2} into half moons. When the potatoes and chicken are 20 mins into their cooking time, remove the baking tray(s) from your oven. Add the pepper and onion and toss so everything is evenly coated in @oil{} (add a little more if necessary). Roast for the remaining ~{15%minutes}.

While everything is cooking, put the @mango chutney{40%g} and @Greek style yoghurt{1%pot} in another small bowl and mix them together. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Put the @honey{1%tbsp} in a #large bowl{}. Squeeze in the lemon juice and add the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then whisk together. Remove the top and bottom from the @cucumber{1}, then thinly slice into rounds. Just before the potatoes, chicken and veggies come out of the oven, add the @pea shoots{2%large handfuls} and cucumber to the bowl with the dressing and toss together.

Once the potatoes, chicken and veggies are cooked, add the parsley and toss to distribute it evenly. Serve on plates with some salad alongside and a spoonful of mango chutney yoghurt. Enjoy!